Name: bipolar ll disorder
Definition: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one hypomanic episode and at least one major depressive episode; with this disorder

Name: bipolar I disorder
Definition: A bipolar disorder that is characterized by at least one manic or mixed episode.

Name: cyclothymic disorder
Definition: A bipolar disorder that involves recurrent hypomanic and dysthymic episodes

Name: obsolete vitamin deficiency
Definition: A bipolar disorder that involves recurrent hypomanic and dysthymic episodes
